cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques for background subtraction in videos captured by moving cameras. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves probabilistic modeling and graph-cut optimization, which are common in the sub-categories of cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses Bayesian filtering, which is a popular technique in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves graph-cut optimization, which is a common technique in cs.GR (Graphics).
